   <conbody>
      <note otherprops="generalM" class="- topic/note ">This menu option is only available if
advanced battery monitor is installed.</note>
      <p class="- topic/p ">The battery monitor test temporarily reduces the rectifier output
to discharge the batteries. The test is completed when 25% of the
total battery capacity is used and the rectifier output automatically
returns to the defined level.</p>
      <note class="- topic/note ">The automatic switch over does not interrupt the output.</note>
      <p class="- topic/p ">To start the battery monitor test:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Hash key</b> to enter the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">User stack</b>. </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Use the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Arrow keys</b> to navigate to <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Battery monitor
test</codeph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Clock/key number 1</b> to start the test.</p>
               <p class="- topic/p ">If you need to interrupt the test while it is running, press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Clock/key number 0</b> to stop the test. </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Back key</b> or wait 30 seconds to exit the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">User stack</b>.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">If the result from the battery monitoring test is within the tolerance
range no alarm is shown in the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b>. If the result is outside
the tolerance range the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows one of the alarms:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Battery monitor warning: The battery capacity is weak. The
batteries have to be replaced soon.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Battery monitor alarm: The battery capacity is gone. The batteries
must be replaced immediately.</p>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </p>
